  "details": "Socat is a relay for bidirectional data transfer between two independent data channels. Each of these data channels may be a file, pipe, device (serial line etc. or a pseudo terminal), a socket (UNIX, IP4, IP6 - raw, UDP, TCP), an SSL socket, proxy CONNECT connection, a file descriptor (stdin etc.), the GNU line editor (readline), a program, or a combination of two of these.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nreadline.sh in socat through 1.8.0.1 relies on the /tmp/$USER/stderr2 file.(CVE-2024-54661)",
